####Github Adding Fail Due TO Bash


Edit or create commitlint.config.js in repo root, e.g.:
module.exports = {
  extends: ['@commitlint/config-conventional'],
  rules: {
    // e.g., allow any subject (not recommended unless you understand consequences)
    'subject-empty': [2, 'never'],
    'type-empty': [2, 'never']
  }
}


Install Git for Windows (if not already installed):
https://git-scm.com/download/win
##For Surety
bash --version

##Path
C:\Program Files\Git\bin
##Environment Variable
Add this folder to your Windows PATH:
Press Windows + S, type environment variables, and open "Edit the system environment variables".
Click Environment Variables….
Under System variables, find Path → Edit → New → paste:
C:\Program Files\Git\bin

##Again For Surety
git add .
git commit -m "chore: mark calendar update as done"



